25 October 2016Deputy Minister of Communications to hand over the Top ICT Youth Leader Award at the inaugural ICT archievers awardsOn Thursday, 27 October 2016, the Deputy Minister of Communications, Ms Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams will participate in the inaugural South African Communications Forum (SACF) ICT Achievers Awards and hand over the Top ICT Youth Leader Award. The ICT Achiever Awards are a celebration of stellar champions of the South African ICT sector, a key sector contributing to our GDP growth and national development. The awards seek to highlight and publicise achievements of the entire ICT Industry and are planned to be a prestigious annual event in the ICT sector. In this respect, top performers in the ICT industry will be awarded in the following categories: 1) Top ICT SMME 2) Top ICT Innovator 3) Top ICT Youth Leader 4) Top Woman in ICT 5) ICT Accessibility Excellence 6) Localisation of ICT 7) Honorary Lifetime Achiever Members of the media are invited to the awards which will take place as follows: Date: Thursday, 27 October 2016 Time: 18h00 for 18h30 Venue: The Galleria, 10 Eastern Service Road, SandtonJournalists will be afforded interviews and photo opportunities. Media RSVPs: Takalani Mukwevho Cell: 082 227 9308 E-mail: takalanim@gcis.gov.za Enquiries: Nthabeleng Mokitimi-Dlamini Cell: 073 222 5522Issued by Ministry of Communication